	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You are wrong. Action Replay MK3 has all pins wired. Chips games do run on the AR MK3. I have one.
<br />
<br />I've never tried using codes on the SGB, but I don't see that working. The GB RAM could be private/unaccessible on the SNES side normally. Unless you've heard otherwise, I don't think it would work. You can however use Gameshark and Game Genie for GB on the SGB.
<br />
<br />Kirby Super Star using the SA-1 chip, so the memory you want to modify may not be accessible by the AR MK3. But the game should still operate through the MK3.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


